OL,6,FThe National Living Wage will rise by
OL,7,F#1.02-an-hour from April, the
OL,8,FTreasury has announced.
OL,10,FThe almost 10% pay boost, from #10.42
OL,11,Fto #11.44 an hour, is the biggest
OL,12,Fincrease in the National Living Wage,
OL,13,Fwhich is currently the minimum hourly
OL,14,Fpay a person over the age of 23 earns
OL,15,Fwhen working, in over a decade.
OL,17,FEligibility for the National Living
OL,18,FWage will also be extended by
OL,19,Freducing the age threshold to 21-year-
OL,20,Folds for the first time.
